<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Nazrin Wraithforge:
[B]What I am disgusted at now is in the high end game the Cleric Epic is becoming more like the manastone was 18 months ago.

All the old hats here think back when you wanted to go on a Planes raid and were turned down over another cleric that had a manastone, what did verant do they nerfed the manastone because of this situation.

What is happening now is clerics are being turned down over clerics with Epics.  This is one of the major drivers as too why MAJORITY of clerics want their sticks its not for the pure eliteness of having this item its actually so they have a better chance at being considered for the high end raids.

The issue with your idiological approach Rayne is that it fully supports the Uber Guild member the guy with no life except that within Everquest.  Casual players who put in the effort according too your ideals should go unrewarded thats just plain wrong.

Secondly the bigger picture is that uber guilds are now abusing this spawn 'How' you ask well they are obtaining epics for twinks for the sack of a backup rezzer what makes me sick is there is many a cleric that is a main character that is missing this spawn because someones third or fourth character is a Rez Whore for an Uber guild.  That is Totally WRONG..  I am sorry but I can't condone this sense of immorality.

Also the comment about Ragefire being more like Lozidal I hate to say this but with you option he is more like him than you first realise.  How so well think of this way I know on many server rangers/druids camp the Lozidal spawn area's waiting for a sign on track the minute he is up they assemble forces and kill him.  Whats so different about a cleric or monk camping the Ragefire only too assemble the forces the minute he spawns.  I say absolutely nothing and the person that sat in a room for however many hours staring at a wall should have first dibs on said kill.  Its a trail of patience not a trial of who can assemble the forces the fastest because the Uber guilds will always win that race.

Should a cleric have to join an Uber Guild for a chance at an epic I should think not. It should be a reward for all the hard work and effort you have put into the game and to those people who stole hearts from other clerics or raced through and gave your pearl ahead of someone else are plainly put Scum.. Who don't deserve to have the tag of a cleric and should be put with all the rogues and Shadowknights of the world.

anyway thats just my 2 cents.

Nazrin[/B][/QUOTE]

